<P>28. Though Wetzel has attempted to mitigate his damages by seeking alternate employment as an appraiser with other companies, the fact that he was dismissed by Aviva on the basis of an alleged fraud forecloses any possibility that he can be rehired. In particular, though Wetzel was able to secure an interview with another insurer (Desjardins), he was unable to secure any position therewith once this new insurer learned of Wetzel's termination. Wetzel is currently unemployed, and sustains himself through his savings and any net income generated from self-directed trading in the capital markets.</P>
<P>29. In addition to compensatory damages arising from lost future income, the plaintiff by counterclaim also seeks moral damages on account of the manner that he was dismissed. Put succinctly, at the time of termination, Wetzel was treated like a dangerous criminal by h is supervisors at Aviva, was publicly humiliated in the process, and was even escorted out of the premises as if he were somehow a danger to the company or its personnel. Accordingly, Wetzel seeks modest moral damages for the mental pain and suffering that he sustained in the manner that he was dismissed.</P>
<P>30. In addition to compensation damages, Wetzel also seeks punitive damages as against Aviva to punish this company for the callous disregard that it showed to his basic human dignity and self -worth at the time of termination. Aviva did not even afford Wetzel an opportunity to explain himself; rather, it concluded that Wetzel was a fraudster and brusquely treated him as such. Such conduct is unacceptable, and amply warrants an award of punitive damages so as to punish this kind of outrageous behaviour.</P>
<P>31. The defendant (plaintiff by counterclaim) pleads that the counterclaim be tried immediately after the hearing of the main action, all in the City of Toronto. However, due to the complexity of the factual and legal issues arising from this proceeding, the jury trial requested by Aviva would be inappropriate, and thus calling for a bench trial only.</P>
